"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-03-23-Mbappe-wants-to-represent-France-in-Paris-Olympics-1scp0T6OVfa-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  French captain Kylian Mbappe expressed his willingness to represent his country at the Paris Olympics this summer, although it will be on a collision course with Spanish club Real Madrid which he is estimated to join after his contract with Paris St Germain (PSG) expires in late June.  La Liga giant Real, who have been at the forefront of chasing the World Cup winner, emailed the French Football Federation that they will not release their players for the Games, including Aurelien Tchouameni and Eduardo Camavinga whom Mbappe will potentially join.  The Olympic football competition is typically an Under-23 tournament, though only three players over the age limit allowed in each squad.  Mbappe, 25, confirmed his willingness to fulfill his obligation to the French side in both Euro 2024 and the Paris Olympics, provided he is allowed to be available for selection.  File photo of Kylian Mbappe. /CFP  \\\"I have always had the same ambition. I have always said that I wanted to go [to the Olympics] but it does not depend on me,\\\" Mbappe said on Friday.  \\\"I can not say anything because no one has told me anything. If I can not do the Olympics so be it ... When I say no one has told me anything, I am talking about PSG. I am under contract with PSG and they have not said anything [about the Olympics]. We have not discussed it,\\\" he added.  The Olympics football tournament will be played from July 24 to August 9, and it's unclear if it will overlap with the 2024/25 La Liga schedule yet to be released.  Last month, Mbappe announced that he will leave Ligue 1 leaders PSG this summer after seven years and five French titles. He has not officially announced joining Real, but expects to clarify his next move before Euro 2024 which starts in mid-June.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"